==English==

===Verb===
{{en-verb|maculat|ing}}

# To [[spot]]; to [[stain]]; to [[blur]].

===Adjective===
'''maculate'''

# Marked with spots or maculae; blotched; hence, defiled; impure; as, most maculate thoughts.

Usage:
:In [[w:The New Republic|The New Republic]], May 25, 1998, [[w:Victor Hugo|Victor Hugo]]'s [[w:Les Misérables|Les Misérables]] is described as being "about the struggle of a mistreated man as he rises to the top, along with a mortal conflict between this ''maculate'' virtuous man and an immaculate pursuing demon."

